## Project Standards

**All AI agents must strictly adhere to these rules.**

### Tooling

| Tool | Purpose |
|:-----|:--------|
| [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) | Package manager — **never** use `pip` or `venv` |
| [Ruff](https://docs.astral.sh/ruff/) | Linting and formatting |
| [ty](https://github.com/astral-sh/ty) | Type checking |
| [pytest](https://pytest.org/) | Testing |

### Dependencies

```bash
uv add <package>              # Production dependency
uv add --dev <package>        # Dev dependency
uv sync                       # Lock dependencies
uv run <cmd>                  # Run commands
```

---

## Code Conventions

### General

- Follow **PEP 8**
- Use **Python 3.10+** syntax
- Keep it simple—avoid over-engineering

### Naming

| Element | Convention |
|:--------|:-----------|
| Variables/Functions | `snake_case` |
| Classes | `CamelCase` |
| Strings | f-strings (`f"..."`) |

### Type Hints

- **Mandatory** for all function signatures (arguments and return types)
- Use modern syntax: `list[str]`, `str | None`
- Validate with: `uvx ty`

### Imports

- Order: stdlib → third-party → local (enforced by Ruff)
- Sort alphabetically within groups
- Use absolute imports
- Fix with: `uv run ruff check --select I --fix .`

### Docstrings

- Google-style for all public functions and classes

### File System

- **Always** use `pathlib.Path`
- **Never** use `os.path.join` or string concatenation

---

## Libraries & Patterns

### Logging (structlog)

- Configure via `setup_logging()` from `{{ package_name }}.logging`
- Create loggers with `structlog.get_logger()`
- Never use `logging` directly

### Settings (Pydantic)

- Location: `src/{{ package_name }}/settings.py`
- Import: `from {{ package_name }}.settings import settings`
- Use `__` delimiter for nesting: `APP__APP_NAME`, `LOGGING__FILE_LEVEL`

### Data Classes vs Pydantic

| Use Case | Choice |
|:---------|:-------|
| Configuration from env vars | `BaseSettings` |
| Simple data containers | `pydantic.dataclass` |
| External data validation | `BaseModel` |
| Immutable DTOs | `@pydantic.dataclass(frozen=True)` |

### CLI (Typer)

- Use **typer** for all entry points

### Async/Await

- Use `async def` only for I/O-bound operations
- Always `await` async calls; never block the event loop
- Use `asyncio.gather()` for concurrent operations
- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` for async HTTP
- Use `asyncio.run()` only in entry points

### Datetime

- **Always** use timezone-aware datetimes
- Use `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` instead of `datetime.utcnow()`
- Serialize with `.isoformat()`; parse with `datetime.fromisoformat()`

### ABC & Protocols

- Use `abc.ABC` for explicit inheritance-based polymorphism
- Use `typing.Protocol` for structural typing (duck typing)
- Mark required methods with `@abstractmethod`

---

## Security

- **Never** hardcode secrets (API keys, passwords, tokens)
- Store secrets in environment variables or `.env` (never commit `.env`)
- Use `pydantic-settings` for secret management
- Never auto-run destructive commands (`rm -rf`, `del /s`, `curl | sh`)
- Respect `.cursorignore` paths (`.env*`, `.ssh/`, `secrets/`)
- Prefer read-only MCP access; avoid broad tokens

---

## Testing

- **Framework**: pytest
- **Location**: `tests/` mirroring project structure
- **Naming**: Functions start with `test_`
- **Fixtures**: Use pytest fixtures (not class-based setup)
- **Rule**: All new features and bug fixes require tests

```bash
uv run pytest
```

---

## Git Workflow

### Rule

**Only create commits when the user explicitly asks. Never commit proactively.**

### Pre-commit

```bash
uv run pre-commit install
```

### Conventional Commits

```
<type>: <description>
```

- Lowercase, concise, no trailing period

| Type | Purpose |
|:-----|:--------|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change without feature/bug change |
| `test` | Test updates |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `chore` | Routine tasks, dependency updates |

### AI-Generated Code

Mark AI-assisted commits with:
```
Co-authored-by: Cursor/opencode/Claude Code
```